Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Note: Bifrost Graph Edge System
Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Note: This module defines the edge system for the Bifrost heterogeneous computing
Note: intermediate representation. Edges represent data flow, control flow, and
Note: dependencies between computational nodes in the Bifrost graph.

Note: Edge Types:
Note: - DataFlow: Value flows from source to destination (SSA def-use)
Note: - Control: Execution order dependency (e.g., barrier synchronization)
Note: - Memory: Memory dependency (load must see store result)
Note: - AntiDep: Anti-dependency (write after read hazard)
Note: - OutputDep: Output dependency (write after write hazard)

Note: Location: compiler/middle/bifrost/graph/edge.runa
Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Import "compiler/middle/bifrost/graph/node.runa"
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as String

Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Note: Edge Kind Type
Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Note: EdgeKind represents the type of dependency between two nodes
Type EdgeKind is:
    | DataFlow    Note: Value flows from source to destination (SSA def-use)
    | Control     Note: Execution order dependency (synchronization)
    | Memory      Note: Memory dependency (load must see store)
    | AntiDep     Note: Anti-dependency (write after read hazard)
    | OutputDep   Note: Output dependency (write after write hazard)
End Type

Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Note: Bifrost Edge Structure
Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@Reasoning:
The BifrostEdge structure represents a directed edge in the Bifrost computation
graph. Each edge connects a source node to a destination node and carries:

- Unique edge identifier for reference tracking
- Source node reference (producer)
- Destination node reference (consumer)
- Edge kind (data flow, control, memory dependency, etc.)
- Data type (for type checking and optimization)
- Optional metadata (annotations, optimization hints)

Memory Layout (OWNED HEAP - Tier 3):
Offset | Size | Field
-------|------|------------------
0      | 8    | Discriminant (always 0 for struct)
8      | 8    | edge_id (Integer)
16     | 8    | source_node (Integer - pointer to BifrostNode)
24     | 8    | dest_node (Integer - pointer to BifrostNode)
32     | 8    | kind (EdgeKind discriminant)
40     | 8    | data_type (Integer - pointer to BifrostType)
48     | 8    | metadata (Integer - pointer to Dictionary)

Total size: 56 bytes
@End Reasoning

Type called "BifrostEdge":
    edge_id as Integer
    source_node as Integer    Note: Pointer to source BifrostNode
    dest_node as Integer      Note: Pointer to destination BifrostNode
    kind as EdgeKind
    data_type as Integer      Note: Pointer to BifrostType (type flowing through edge)
    metadata as Integer       Note: Pointer to Dictionary[String, String] (optional annotations)
End Type

Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Note: Edge Construction and Management
Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@Reasoning:
The factory enforces the BifrostEdge invariant that every edge carries a complete
producer/consumer triple plus a typed-payload tag at construction time. By taking
the kind enum directly the call site can never elide the dependency classification
that scheduling and alias analysis rely on, and metadata is intentionally left null
to keep the 56-byte struct lean for graphs with millions of edges.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates a 56-byte BifrostEdge on the OWNED HEAP tier, writes the struct
discriminant (0), edge_id, source/destination node pointers, the EdgeKind
discriminant via Match, the data_type pointer, and zero-initialises metadata.
Layout.memory_set_int64 is used for each field so the layout matches the offset
table documented in the BifrostEdge struct comment exactly.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(1) heap allocation plus 7 64-bit stores; no I/O, no recursion. Hot path for
graph construction so the EdgeKind Match should compile to a small dispatch
table. Caller should batch creations within a single arena scope when possible
to amortise allocator overhead.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
OWNED HEAP allocation, no capability requirements. Caller must supply validated
source_node, dest_node, and data_type pointers - this routine performs no
liveness or type-compatibility checks. metadata is intentionally null so no
borrowed pointers are aliased into the new edge.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "create_edge" that takes
    edge_id as Integer,
    source_node as Integer,
    dest_node as Integer,
    kind as EdgeKind,
    data_type as Integer
    returns Integer:

    Note: Allocate 56 bytes for BifrostEdge on OWNED HEAP
    Let edge be Layout.memory_allocate(56)

    Note: Set discriminant to 0 (struct type)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 0, 0)

    Note: Set edge_id
    Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 8, edge_id)

    Note: Set source_node pointer
    Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 16, source_node)

    Note: Set dest_node pointer
    Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 24, dest_node)

    Note: Set edge kind discriminant
    Match kind:
        When DataFlow:
            Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 32, 0)
        When Control:
            Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 32, 1)
        When Memory:
            Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 32, 2)
        When AntiDep:
            Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 32, 3)
        When OutputDep:
            Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 32, 4)
    End Match

    Note: Set data_type pointer
    Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 40, data_type)

    Note: Initialize metadata to null (no metadata by default)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 48, 0)

    Return edge
End Process

Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Note: Edge Source Node Management
Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@Reasoning:
Allowing the source endpoint to be retargeted lets passes such as kernel fusion
and op reordering rewire dataflow without destroying and rebuilding the edge,
preserving the edge_id which downstream analyses key dependency maps on.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Performs a null-guard on the edge pointer, then writes the new source pointer
at offset 16. Pure 64-bit store via Layout.memory_set_int64; no allocation or
discriminant change.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(1) - one branch and one 64-bit store. Inlinable in tight rewrite loops.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Caller must ensure new_source points to a live BifrostNode; the helper does
not validate node liveness. Null edge is tolerated as a no-op rather than a
fault so cleanup paths can be uniformly written.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "set_edge_source" that takes edge as Integer, new_source as Integer returns Nothing:
    If edge is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Note: Update source_node pointer at offset 16
    Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 16, new_source)
End Process

@Reasoning:
Pure accessor that hides the offset-16 layout choice from analysis passes so the
struct can be reorganised without touching every consumer that needs the producer
endpoint.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns 0 for null edge pointers, otherwise reads the source_node pointer from
offset 16 via Layout.memory_get_int64.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(1) load. Trivially inlinable; compiles to a single mov in the optimised path.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Pure read. Returns 0 sentinel on null edge so def-use walkers do not need to
guard before calling.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_edge_source" that takes edge as Integer returns Integer:
    If edge is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Read source_node pointer from offset 16
    Let source be Layout.memory_get_int64(edge, 16)
    Return source
End Process

Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Note: Edge Destination Node Management
Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@Reasoning:
Retargeting the consumer side is required when peephole fusion redirects a
downstream consumer or when verifier-level repair patches a stale edge. Keeping
the operation in-place preserves edge_id-keyed bookkeeping in the graph index.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-guards the edge pointer, then writes the new destination pointer at the
offset-24 slot using Layout.memory_set_int64.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(1); single branch plus single 64-bit store.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Caller must guarantee new_dest references a live BifrostNode; no liveness check
here. Null edge is silently ignored to keep rewrite paths uniform.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "set_edge_dest" that takes edge as Integer, new_dest as Integer returns Nothing:
    If edge is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Note: Update dest_node pointer at offset 24
    Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 24, new_dest)
End Process

@Reasoning:
Symmetric to get_edge_source - hides the offset-24 layout decision so analyses
can be authored against the consumer endpoint without binding to byte offsets.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns 0 on null edge; otherwise reads the destination pointer from offset 24.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(1) load, single 64-bit read; trivially inlinable.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Pure read. Null-safe; caller must still validate the returned pointer before
dereferencing it.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_edge_dest" that takes edge as Integer returns Integer:
    If edge is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Read dest_node pointer from offset 24
    Let dest be Layout.memory_get_int64(edge, 24)
    Return dest
End Process

Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Note: Edge Kind Management
Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@Reasoning:
The kind drives scheduling, hazard-detection, and codegen barrier emission, so
in-place reclassification is occasionally required (for example when memory
analysis promotes a tentative DataFlow into a Memory dependency). Mutating in
place keeps consumer indexes valid.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
After null-guarding the edge, the EdgeKind enum is lowered to its discriminant
(0=DataFlow .. 4=OutputDep) using a Match block and written at offset 32 with
Layout.memory_set_int64.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(1) - one branch, one 5-way Match, one 64-bit store. Match compiles to a small
jump table; safe for tight rewrite loops.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Pure metadata mutation; no aliasing concerns. The Match is exhaustive over
EdgeKind so out-of-range discriminants cannot be written.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "set_edge_kind" that takes edge as Integer, new_kind as EdgeKind returns Nothing:
    If edge is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Note: Convert EdgeKind to discriminant and store at offset 32
    Match new_kind:
        When DataFlow:
            Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 32, 0)
        When Control:
            Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 32, 1)
        When Memory:
            Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 32, 2)
        When AntiDep:
            Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 32, 3)
        When OutputDep:
            Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 32, 4)
    End Match
End Process

@Reasoning:
Exposes the kind discriminant as the type-safe EdgeKind enum so passes can drive
Match dispatch directly. Defensive defaulting to DataFlow on null or invalid
discriminants keeps schedulers from crashing on partially-built graphs that the
verifier has not yet examined.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns DataFlow when the edge pointer is null. Otherwise reads the discriminant
at offset 32 and maps 0..4 to DataFlow/Control/Memory/AntiDep/OutputDep with a
linear If-chain, falling back to DataFlow for unrecognised values.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(1) - one load plus up to five compares. The discriminant compare cascade is
shorter than a Match and stays in a few cache-resident instructions.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Pure read; null-safe; out-of-range discriminants are mapped to DataFlow rather
than propagated, which is the safe choice for scheduling (treat as ordinary
dataflow until verifier repairs the edge).
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_edge_kind" that takes edge as Integer returns EdgeKind:
    If edge is equal to 0:
        Return DataFlow
    End If

    Note: Read kind discriminant from offset 32
    Let kind_discriminant be Layout.memory_get_int64(edge, 32)

    Note: Map discriminant to EdgeKind enum
    If kind_discriminant is equal to 0:
        Return DataFlow
    End If
    If kind_discriminant is equal to 1:
        Return Control
    End If
    If kind_discriminant is equal to 2:
        Return Memory
    End If
    If kind_discriminant is equal to 3:
        Return AntiDep
    End If
    If kind_discriminant is equal to 4:
        Return OutputDep
    End If

    Note: Invalid discriminant - return safe default
    Return DataFlow
End Process

Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Note: Edge Data Type Management
Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@Reasoning:
Type refinement (e.g. promoting a generic vector edge to a concrete f32x4 after
specialisation) requires retagging the payload type without re-allocating the
edge. The setter keeps consumer indexes stable.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-guards the edge pointer then writes the BifrostType pointer at offset 40.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(1) store; safe to call in inner refinement loops.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Caller must guarantee new_type points to a live BifrostType; this routine does
not check compatibility between the producer's output type and new_type - the
verifier pass is responsible for that contract.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "set_edge_data_type" that takes edge as Integer, new_type as Integer returns Nothing:
    If edge is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Note: Update data_type pointer at offset 40
    Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 40, new_type)
End Process

@Reasoning:
Exposes the payload type for type-checking, kernel-fusion compatibility checks,
and codegen. Layout-isolating accessor keeps consumers stable across struct
reorganisation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-guards the edge pointer and returns the data_type pointer stored at offset
40, or 0 when the edge is null.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(1) load.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Pure read. Returned pointer may be 0 (unset) or a live BifrostType; caller must
distinguish before dereferencing.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_edge_data_type" that takes edge as Integer returns Integer:
    If edge is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Read data_type pointer from offset 40
    Let dtype be Layout.memory_get_int64(edge, 40)
    Return dtype
End Process

Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Note: Edge Metadata Management
Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@Reasoning:
Metadata is a sparse side-channel for optimisation hints (e.g. "speculative",
"cross-device"), profiling counters, and verifier annotations. Attaching it to
the edge rather than a global side table keeps locality for analyses that walk
edges, and zero remains a valid "no metadata" sentinel.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-guards the edge pointer then stores the metadata dictionary pointer at
offset 48 with Layout.memory_set_int64.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(1) store. Metadata is touched infrequently; not a hot path.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Caller owns the lifetime of the metadata dictionary; assigning a borrowed
dictionary that is later freed will cause use-after-free in consumers. Pass 0
to clear.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "set_edge_metadata" that takes edge as Integer, metadata as Integer returns Nothing:
    If edge is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Note: Update metadata pointer at offset 48
    Layout.memory_set_int64(edge, 48, metadata)
End Process

@Reasoning:
Sparse-channel accessor. Returning 0 for both null-edge and unset-metadata cases
gives consumers a uniform "no annotation" check.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns 0 on null edge; otherwise loads the metadata pointer from offset 48.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(1) load. Off the hot edge-traversal path; only invoked by passes that consult
hints.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Pure read. Returned pointer is borrowed - caller must not free it; the dictionary
is owned by the edge's allocator scope.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_edge_metadata" that takes edge as Integer returns Integer:
    If edge is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Read metadata pointer from offset 48
    Let meta be Layout.memory_get_int64(edge, 48)
    Return meta
End Process

Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Note: Edge Debugging and Utilities
Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@Reasoning:
Debug-only stringifier that materialises a stable, grep-friendly representation
of every edge for verifier dumps and pass-pipeline logs. Hex-formatting node and
type pointers preserves identity across runs while staying compact.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns "[NULL EDGE]" for null. Otherwise reads edge_id, source, dest,
kind_discriminant, and data_type fields, maps the discriminant to its kind name
via a linear If-cascade, hex-encodes the three pointer fields, and concatenates
into the canonical "Edge #id: Node src -> Node dest (kind, type=type)" form.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(1) field reads plus O(L) string concatenation where L is the formatted length
(~60 chars). Multiple intermediate String allocations - do not call inside
inner-loop scheduling code; restrict to diagnostics.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
Pure read; null-safe. No information-disclosure concerns since the output is
intended for compiler-internal logs. Hex pointer values are leaked into strings,
so callers should not forward edge_to_string output to untrusted sinks.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "edge_to_string" that takes edge as Integer returns String:
    If edge is equal to 0:
        Return "[NULL EDGE]"
    End If

    Note: Read edge fields
    Let edge_id be Layout.memory_get_int64(edge, 8)
    Let source be Layout.memory_get_int64(edge, 16)
    Let dest be Layout.memory_get_int64(edge, 24)
    Let kind_discriminant be Layout.memory_get_int64(edge, 32)
    Let dtype be Layout.memory_get_int64(edge, 40)

    Note: Convert edge kind discriminant to string
    Let kind_str be ""
    If kind_discriminant is equal to 0:
        Set kind_str to "DataFlow"
    End If
    If kind_discriminant is equal to 1:
        Set kind_str to "Control"
    End If
    If kind_discriminant is equal to 2:
        Set kind_str to "Memory"
    End If
    If kind_discriminant is equal to 3:
        Set kind_str to "AntiDep"
    End If
    If kind_discriminant is equal to 4:
        Set kind_str to "OutputDep"
    End If

    Note: Convert pointers to hex strings for debugging
    Let source_hex be String.int_to_hex(source)
    Let dest_hex be String.int_to_hex(dest)
    Let type_hex be String.int_to_hex(dtype)

    Note: Construct debug string
    Let result be "Edge #"
    Set result to String.concatenate(result, String.from_int(edge_id))
    Set result to String.concatenate(result, ": Node ")
    Set result to String.concatenate(result, source_hex)
    Set result to String.concatenate(result, " -> Node ")
    Set result to String.concatenate(result, dest_hex)
    Set result to String.concatenate(result, " (")
    Set result to String.concatenate(result, kind_str)
    Set result to String.concatenate(result, ", type=")
    Set result to String.concatenate(result, type_hex)
    Set result to String.concatenate(result, ")")

    Return result
End Process

Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Note: End of Edge System Implementation
Note: ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
